revision.text:
'''Anianus ''' was an Egyptian monk who lived at the beginning of the [[5th century AD]] and wrote a chronography in which, according to the later chronicler [[George Syncellus]], he generally followed [[Eusebius]], but sometimes corrected errors made by that writer. It is, however, very doubtful whether Anianus, on the whole, surpassed Eusebius in accuracy. Syncellus frequently finds fault with him.<ref>[[George Syncellus]], ''Chronogr.'' pp. 7, 16, 17, 34-36.</ref>

