'''Kenny Smyth''', played by [[Shane Jacobson]], is an Australian [[fictional character]]. Jacobson portrays Smyth as an amiable chummy type of person with a slightly gruff, but extremely cheerful character. Smyth appeared in the 2006 film ''[[Kenny (2006 film)|Kenny]]'' and the TV series ''[[Kenny's World]]''.

==Character biography==
Smyth grew up on an orchard in Northern [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]].

===''Kenny''===
{{See also|Kenny (2006 film)}}
The film is about Kenny's life as a plumber and his personal life. He works at Melbourne's biggest events including the [[St Kilda Festival]], [[Avalon Airshow]] and [[Melbourne Cup]]. He also goes to the World Toilet and Plumbers Expo in [[Nashville]] where he meets the love of his life, Jackie.

===''Kenny's World''===
{{See also|Kenny's World}}
The TV series is about Smyth traveling the world to find out about toilets internationally. He visits countries in Africa, Asia, Europe and North America.

===Other appearances===
Smyth has appeared in Australian shows including ''[[20 to 01]]'' and [[The Panel (Australian TV series)|''The Panel'']] Christmas Wrap 2006.
